{
  "narration": "Kira draws a deep breath, her silhouette tense and ready as twilight thickens around you. 'All right, Eirik. No more detours. Let's see what these bandits are hiding.'\n\nWith shortbow in hand, she leads the way down the narrowing trail, senses sharpened by the encroaching dark. The path twists through dense brambles, the only sounds your measured footsteps and the distant, anxious rustle of wings. The oppressive hush of the Thornwood presses in, lending every shadow a dangerous weight.\n\nAs you draw closer to the stronghold, Kira pauses, holding up a hand. 'We're getting close. Keep your shield ready, and let's move quiet.'\n\nYou slip forward, the forest falling utterly silent behind you. Just ahead, through the tangled undergrowth, the outline of a crumbling stone tower looms in the night, firelight flickering in a few arrow slits and the faint sound of rough voices drifting from within. You're at the threshold--the bandit stronghold lies before you, secrets and dangers within its battered walls.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "transitionLocation",
      "parameters": {
        "newLocation": "TW05"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 8
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updatePlot",
      "parameters": {
        "plotPointId": "PP002",
        "newStatus": "in progress",
        "plotImpact": "Eirik and Kira have reached the bandit stronghold at nightfall, preparing to scout the heart of the enemy's operations and uncover Malarok's plans."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The night air hangs heavy with tension as you and Kira crouch at the edge of tangled undergrowth, gazing up at the looming silhouette of the bandit stronghold. The old watchtower's cracked stone walls rise above the brambles, flickering firelight leaking through narrow arrow slits. Somewhere within, rough voices murmur and laugh, oblivious to your silent approach.\n\nKira shifts beside you, her bowstring taut, eyes fixed on the battered doorway partially obscured by brush. 'This is it, Eirik,' she whispers. 'If we want to slip in unnoticed, now's our chance. Or we can wait, see if any patrols return, or even try to draw someone out. What do you think?'\n\nThe Thornwood behind you is a sea of darkness and secrets, but every sense tells you this is the enemy's heart. The next move is yours. Will you attempt a stealthy infiltration, call out to bait a response, or watch the bandit stronghold for a while longer? Kira glances at you, determination and trust shining in her eyes, ready to follow your lead.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira narrows her eyes, surveying the crude palisade walls and ancient stonework, her breath barely stirring the night air. 'There's the palisade gate with those heavy crossbeams,' she whispers, gesturing subtly. 'Looks solid--locked, most likely, and no telling how many are stationed behind it.'\n\nShe leans closer, voice low. 'But look there, Eirik--see that section where the wall meets the old oak? Some of the logs are cracked, and the ground looks softer. Might be a weak point if we want to try climbing or prying our way in, but it's right in sight of one of those lookout posts. If we go for stealth, we'll have to be careful not to get spotted by the sentries.'\n\nHer eyes flick to the darkened approach, where the shadows are thickest. 'We could work our way around behind the brambles, look for a hidden way in, or even try to cause a distraction. Or I could try to get up a tree and pick off a sentry when no one's looking. What do you think? Risk a climb, try to draw them out, or check for a hidden entrance?'\n\nShe pauses, frowning with concern. 'Just... watch your step. If there's going to be a pit trap, it'll be right along the main approach. Nothing like a few sharpened stakes to spoil our night.'\n\nWhat do you want to do, Eirik? Scout for a weak spot, try to lure someone out, attempt a climb, or something else? Let me know, and we'll face whatever's inside together.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira lowers herself closer to the ground, peering through the brambles at the flicker of firelight and the shifting silhouettes inside the stronghold. Her keen eyes dart from one lookout post to the next as she studies the fortifications.\n\n'I'd wager at least six,' she whispers, voice barely above the rustle of leaves. 'There's always a pair of sentries up in those trees, and I've seen three or four more moving near the fire pit and the main gate. But that big half-orc in armor--the one with the glowing eyes? He's their captain, and he won't be an easy mark.'\n\nShe glances sidelong at you, her confidence tinged with tension. 'If they've got more inside the tower, we might be talking seven or eight, but most look like they're hunkered down around the fire or patrolling the walls. We definitely can't take them all at once. If we move careful and pick off a sentry, we might slip in and cause a distraction, but if they raise the alarm, we'll have the whole nest on us.'\n\nKira pauses, then points to the path near the gate. 'That patch of ground looks off--sunken a bit, no leaves. Classic spot for a pit trap. I'd bet silver there's one waiting for us right by the main approach.'\n\nShe looks to you expectantly. 'What's your call, Eirik? Sneak in, draw them out, or try to find a way to thin their numbers first?'",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira nods grimly, a sly grin flickering across her face. 'I like your thinking, Eirik. A little chaos in the night might give us the edge.'\n\nShe crouches low, scanning the stronghold's perimeter for sentries, her eyes flickering between the lookout posts and the main fire pit beyond the wall. 'We could use the darkness to our advantage. Maybe shoot an arrow to spook the horses, light up some supplies, or mimic an animal call to lure a sentry out. If we make them think something's wrong beyond the walls, one or two might come to investigate, and that's when we strike.'\n\nKira glances back at you for affirmation. 'I can handle the bow work, but you might want to ready a spell just in case things go loud. When you're set, I'll pick my moment and let fly. Let's make them nervous.'\n\nShe settles into position behind a fallen log, nocking an arrow and waiting for your signal. The torches flicker in the distance, and the sounds of banter carry on the night air. All that's needed now is the first move.\n\nEirik, how do you want to draw them out? A distraction, a whispered call, or perhaps a torch tossed into their supplies? Let me know your plan, and Kira will follow your lead.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira nods, her lips quirking in a quiet smirk. 'All right, let's see if we can peel one away from their post.'\n\nShe slips silently through the undergrowth to get a clear line of sight on the nearest lookout, an arrow nocked and ready. You prepare yourself, flattening behind a tangle of brambles as you scan for any sign that your plan has been noticed. Kira draws a smooth breath, then imitates the sharp, urgent bark of a fox from the darkness--a call perfectly suited to the Thornwood but unusual enough to catch the bandits' attention.\n\nMoments later, a torch flares at the edge of the palisade. One of the sentries peers out, muttering a curse as he steps closer to the wall, searching the darkness. He calls over his shoulder, 'Probably them damn animals again... I'll check it out.'\n\nThe sentry climbs down from the lookout post and slips through a narrow service gate, his crossbow at the ready as he steps into the brush, squinting in your direction. He's alone, separated from the others by the wall. Kira gives you a sharp nod, her eyes asking if you want her to take the shot now or if you want to try something else.\n\nEirik, do you want Kira to loose her arrow as soon as the sentry is clear, or would you rather try to subdue him quietly? Act quickly--any delay might risk him spotting you both or calling for backup.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira keeps her gaze fixed on the lone sentry as he edges further from the stronghold, her breath steady. In a low whisper, she responds, 'I'm quick with a blade, but when I'm unseen, I hit hardest. If I strike from the shadows, I can land a sneak attack--it lets me drive the point home where it hurts most. If he doesn't know I'm here, that first shot will sting twice as bad.'\n\nHer fingers tighten on the bowstring, voice barely audible. 'I can slip past most folk without a sound, and if he gets close, I can use my Cunning Action to duck away or get behind him before he can shout.'\n\nShe gives you a quick, reassuring smirk, confidence gleaming in her green eyes. 'Just help me keep him off balance, and I'll make it quick and quiet. If you want to take him alive, let me know--otherwise, I'll aim to drop him before he can call for help.'\n\nThe sentry pauses, peering warily at the shadows. Now is the moment to decide, Eirik: do you want Kira to take the shot and use her sneak attack, or do you want to try to capture the sentry for information? Either way, you'll need to act now before he grows suspicious or calls out.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira flashes a quick, wolfish grin and melts deeper into the shadows, drawing her bow in utter silence. The sentry, unaware of the danger stalking him, edges closer to the brush in search of the source of the fox's call. His crossbow is raised, but his attention is scattered, his posture betraying a hint of boredom.\n\nWith the sentry alone and out of sight of the main stronghold, Kira takes a slow, measured breath. You catch the subtle glint of determination in her eyes. She looses her arrow, aiming for the vital spot behind the bandit's collarbone, using her rogue training to strike with deadly precision while unseen.\n\nLet's resolve Kira's attack: She rolls with advantage thanks to her stealth and the sentry's lack of awareness.\n\nKira's attack roll: d20 (15) and d20 (10), taking the higher result: 15. With her +5 attack bonus, that's a total of 20--a solid hit! Her sneak attack damage: 1d6 (bow) + 1d6 (sneak attack) = 3 + 4 = 7. Add her Dexterity modifier (+3), for a total of 10 piercing damage.\n\nThe arrow thuds home with a muffled grunt. The sentry staggers, clutching his side, barely remaining upright but clearly gravely wounded, his crossbow falling into the brush. He gasps for breath, panic flaring in his eyes, but he's still on his feet--for now.\n\nEirik, you see the sentry start to lurch back toward the gate, his voice catching in his throat as he tries to call out. You have a split second to act before he can raise the alarm! If you follow up with your mace or another action, now's the time to move in.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You surge from the brambles, boots crunching softly in the leaf litter as the wounded sentry wheels toward you, panic flaring in his eyes. He tries to shout, but your mace is already arcing downward. The torchlight from the stronghold flickers over his pale, sweat-streaked face.\n\nPlease make an attack roll with your mace. Roll a d20 and add your attack bonus (+4). If you succeed, you'll be able to finish off the sentry before he can raise the alarm.\n\nQuick, Eirik -- your window is narrow before the camp is alerted. Let me know your roll!",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Your mace comes crashing down with precise, desperate force. The sentry--already reeling from Kira's arrow--barely has time to raise his hand before the heavy blow lands squarely on his head. There's a sharp crack, a muffled gasp, and he crumples silently into the brush, unconscious before he even hits the ground.\n\nKira rises from the shadows, eyes wide and alert. She gives you a brief nod of approval and quickly drags the sentry's body further into the undergrowth, checking his pulse. 'He's out cold. That was clean, Eirik.' She swiftly relieves him of his crossbow, quiver, and a small pouch of coins. 'Looks like he won't be raising any alarms tonight.'\n\nThe air around the stronghold holds its tense hush, none the wiser for your swift and silent takedown. For now, you've managed to thin their numbers without alerting the rest.\n\nKira whispers, 'One down. We can watch their routine or try to draw another out, or... we slip in now while they're missing a sentry. Your call, Eirik. What next?'",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Successfully knocked out a bandit sentry with a mace. No damage taken."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout kira",
        "changes": "Recovered crossbow and quiver from downed sentry. Acquired a small pouch of coins."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira crouches beside you, eyes narrowed as she peers through the tangled undergrowth toward the stronghold's perimeter. The torchlight from the fire pit flickers across the palisade, and the sounds of rough laughter echo faintly from deeper within. She whispers, 'Let me get a better look.'\n\nMoving with practiced stealth, Kira glides a few paces up the tree line, scanning the lookout posts and open ground near the gate. Her sharp eyes spot another sentry--a burly figure silhouetted on a raised platform just above the palisade, idly scanning the dark, his crossbow resting on the rail. He hasn't noticed that his companion is missing yet, and doesn't look especially alert, but a wrong move could draw his gaze.\n\nKira returns and murmurs, 'The second sentry's above the gate, watching the path. He's got a clear view of anyone coming in, but not much else. If we want to take him, we need to move fast and quiet, or lure him down like we did the last one.'\n\nShe glances at you, a sly smile on her lips. 'Should I try another distraction, or do you have a plan for getting him down from that perch?'",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira flashes a quick, appreciative grin as you bring up the sentry. 'Good catch, Eirik. Every small victory counts, and so does every lesson.'\n\nYou both feel a subtle surge of satisfaction--the kind that comes from outwitting a dangerous foe without spilling more blood than needed. The night's tension doesn't quite fade, but the sense of accomplishment strengthens your resolve for the challenges ahead.\n\nAs you press on, the second sentry remains at his post above the gate, oblivious to the fate of his comrade. The stronghold is still alive with the distant sounds of laughter and clinking mugs, but the odds are tipping ever so slightly in your favor.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Gained 50 XP for helping to defeat the bandit sentry outside the stronghold; XP is now 350/900."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout kira",
        "changes": "Gained 50 XP for helping to defeat the bandit sentry outside the stronghold; XP is now 350/900."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira glances back, her eyes reflecting the flicker of torchlight from the stronghold. She studies the path toward the sentry's perch above the gate, the stakes higher with every step. 'He's not as alert as he should be,' she whispers, 'but this is still risky. We'll need to move fast and close--the darkness helps, but if one of the warriors at the fire looks up, we're exposed.'\n\nShe leans close, voice barely above a breath. 'If we stick to the brush and time the approach for when someone's stoking the fire or passing a jug, we might get close enough. I'll try to circle left, using the shadow of that big oak. You hug the palisade and come straight in as soon as I signal.'\n\nKira narrows her eyes at the platform and the flickering light, calculating the gaps between patrols. 'It's tight, but if anyone can do it, we can. But Eirik, you need to move quietly--no armor clanking, keep low and watch for loose branches.'\n\nShe fixes you with a determined look. 'Ready? You'll need to make a Stealth check. Roll a d20 and add your Stealth modifier (with your scale mail, remember you have disadvantage). Let me know both results. I'll move at the same time, and if he spots us, I'll be ready to cover you.'",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira gives an understanding nod, a sly glint in her eyes. 'Good call, Eirik. Let me handle this. I'm quieter on my own, and if I strike from the shadows, he'll never know what hit him.'\n\nShe checks her footing, fingers running along her yew ward charm for luck, and melts into the darkness along the palisade's edge. You watch her movements--fluid and nearly silent, using the cover of an ancient oak and the shifting torchlight to her advantage. The sentry above the gate is unaware, lost in his own boredom, his crossbow propped on the railing.\n\nKira creeps closer, keeping low and choosing every step with practiced care. Now, let's see how well she slips through the shadows...",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You reach out and murmur a quiet prayer, your holy symbol cool beneath your palm as you invoke a blessing. Silvery energy flickers at your fingertips, then softly settles over Kira like a gentle veil. She glances back at you, gratitude glimmering in her eyes. 'Thanks, Eirik. Every bit of luck helps,' she breathes, then melts into the darkness, lighter on her feet and more confident with your divine aid strengthening her.\n\nKira draws closer to the sentry's perch, timing her ascent with a lull in the noise from the stronghold's fire pit. Her movements are nearly soundless as she slips from shadow to shadow, ready to unleash a deadly attack from concealment.\n\nWith Guidance, Kira rolls a Stealth check: her d20 comes up 13, plus her Stealth bonus (+6) and the Guidance die (1d4: 3), for a total of 22. She glides through the shadows, unseen by the sentry above.\n\nKira positions herself directly beneath the platform. Drawing her shortsword, she waits for the sentry to peer away, then climbs up and strikes with all the precision of a trained rogue, aiming for a swift takedown with her sneak attack.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout kira",
        "changes": "Received Guidance from Eirik, +1d4 to next ability check. Used Stealth to approach sentry with a total roll of 22. Positioned for sneak attack with shortsword."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You whisper a final word of encouragement as Kira melts into the darkness, your faith in her clear. The soft scrape of her boots on wood is all but lost amid the distant laughter and clinking mugs from the stronghold's heart. She climbs swiftly, her silhouette barely visible as she glides onto the platform behind the distracted sentry.\n\nThe sentry leans out, peering into the woods, utterly unaware. In a single, fluid motion, Kira draws her shortsword and strikes from the shadows, aiming straight for a vital spot below the ribs--a textbook sneak attack.\n\nKira's attack roll is 16 (d20) + 5 (attack bonus) = 21--a decisive hit. Her damage: shortsword 1d6 (4), sneak attack 1d6 (5), plus 3 Dexterity modifier, for a total of 12 piercing damage. The sentry barely gasps before collapsing silently across the rail. Kira drags the body into the shadowed corner of the platform, stripping the crossbow, coins, and any loose gear for later inspection.\n\nA faint smile crosses her face as she signals you from above--a single, reassuring thumbs-up.\n\nWith both sentries down and no alarm raised, you and Kira have a real chance to approach the stronghold undetected. Below, the concealed pit trap still yawns near the main gate, and the fire's glow marks where at least three more bandits and their captain gather. From her vantage point, Kira can now scout the interior and report back on weak points or movement.\n\nWhat do you want to do next, Eirik? Join her at the wall, try to slip inside, or take a moment to regroup and plan your next move under cover of darkness?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout kira",
        "changes": "Eliminated second bandit sentry with a successful sneak attack. Looted crossbow, coins, and gear. Remains hidden on the platform above the gate."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You slip through the shadows of the palisade, hugging the wall as you make your way toward the gate platform. The earth beneath your boots is soft but treacherous--Kira flashes a quick, silent warning and points to a patch of sunken ground just off the main approach. You skirt the concealed pit trap, recalling her earlier advice, and in moments are climbing the rough-hewn logs up to join her above the stronghold gate.\n\nKira crouches beside you, wiping her blade clean and keeping a careful watch on the scene below. From this vantage point, you can clearly see the central fire pit where three bandit warriors share drinks and muttered boasts. Their leader, a hulking half-orc in battered armor--his eyes glinting with an unsettling, unnatural green--paces restlessly at the edge of the firelight. Stolen goods and crates bearing strange symbols are stacked against the wall, and the tension in the camp is thick with the sense that something darker than mere banditry festers here.\n\nKira whispers, barely audible, 'We did it, Eirik. If we move quickly, we can attack from above or slip inside while they're distracted. That captain looks like real trouble--if things go wrong, we'll need to be ready to fight or retreat.'\n\nThe night is on your side, but every second counts. What will you do: ambush the warriors from your high perch, attempt to slip into the heart of the stronghold unseen, or try something bolder? Kira looks to you, trusting your next move as your window of surprise rapidly narrows.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira grins with a glint of relief as you mention the experience. 'Can't let a good ambush go unrewarded, can we?' she murmurs. 'You did well, Eirik. That sort of teamwork deserves more than just a pat on the back.'\n\nAs you both crouch on the platform above the stronghold gate, the sense of accomplishment bolsters your confidence for the dangerous moments ahead. You feel that bit closer to your next milestone, the lessons of patience and precision hard-earned in the Thornwood night.\n\nFrom your vantage, you see the bandit warriors below, one tossing a bone into the fire, another sharpening a blade, and Captain Gorvek pacing with restless aggression. For now, your presence remains undetected, but with every breath the window for action narrows.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Gained 100 XP for defeating both bandit sentries without raising the alarm; XP now 450/900."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout kira",
        "changes": "Gained 100 XP for defeating both bandit sentries without raising the alarm; XP now 450/900."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira keeps low beside you atop the gate platform, green eyes scanning the stronghold's firelit interior. The wind shifts, carrying scraps of conversation and the clatter of tin mugs. She leans in, her voice a breath against your ear. 'I count three more around the fire--look, see that one with the scarred cheek, and the two younger ones passing the bottle? They're warriors. That makes five, if you count the captain still pacing by the crates.'\n\nShe points with the tip of her arrow. 'We already dealt with both sentries; their posts are empty now. So it's just the three warriors and Gorvek, their captain. Four left inside these walls, unless anyone's hiding in the tower--but the way they're clustered, doesn't look like they're expecting trouble.'\n\nKira's grip tightens on her bow. 'But Gorvek... something's off about him. Those symbols on his armor, the way his eyes glint--he's not just muscle. If we attack, we need to hit hard and fast, or they'll rally.'\n\nFrom your vantage, you see the firelight glint off battered armor, the uneasy faces of the bandits, and the restless shadow of their leader. You have the upper hand for now--but every second in the open risks discovery. Kira glances at you, concern flickering in her gaze. 'What's our move, Eirik? Strike, sneak, or wait?'",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The chill of the Thornwood night settles around you atop the stronghold gate, the firelight casting restless shadows across the camp below. Kira crouches at your side, her bowstring taut, breath clouding in the cool air as she waits for your signal. Below, three bandit warriors laugh and jeer around the fire while Captain Gorvek, marked by the unnatural green gleam in his eyes, paces among crates of ill-gotten loot.\n\nThe sentries you and Kira dispatched remain undiscovered, their posts empty and the camp's attention turned inward. The thick silence is broken only by the flicker of flames and the occasional bark of laughter from the warriors.\n\nKira glances over, her voice barely a whisper. 'We're still unseen, Eirik. If we're going to act, now's the time. Do we rain arrows from above, slip down for a quick strike, or try to catch them by surprise another way? Just say the word.'\n\nThe final assault on the bandit stronghold hangs on your next move. What will you do?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You murmur a steady prayer, gripping your holy symbol as you call forth a shimmering ward of divine power over Kira. A faint silver radiance surrounds her, weaving into her leathers and forming a protective shield just beneath the skin. Kira glances back, catching the glow at the edge of her vision, and flashes you a grateful, determined smile. 'With you at my back, Eirik, I'll be twice as bold.'\n\nThe camp below remains oblivious, but the moment crackles with tension as you ready yourselves for the chaos to come. Kira's AC is now bolstered by your blessing, and she is prepared to weather whatever the bandits throw her way.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Cast 'Shield of Faith' on Kira. Reduced Level 1 spell slots by 1 (now 2/3)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout kira",
        "changes": "Gained 'Shield of Faith' effect: +2 AC for up to 10 minutes, concentration required by Eirik."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
