{
  "narration": "You rest a steady hand on Kira's shoulder, murmuring another brief prayer. A silvery light flickers over her, Guidance flowing quietly from your holy symbol to her nimble hands. Kira nods with fierce appreciation, the light glinting in her eyes. 'Let's see if we can make this count,' she whispers.\n\nShe melts down from the gate platform, moving like a whisper through the torch shadows. Picking her target--a bandit warrior who has momentarily wandered from the group to adjust his boots by a stack of crates--she draws her shortsword, every muscle wound for a swift, silent strike.\n\nWith Guidance and her rogue expertise, Kira makes her move: Stealth check d20 (14) + 6, plus Guidance d4 (2), for a total of 22. She is utterly unseen as she slips behind the unsuspecting bandit. Her attack roll: d20 (17) + 5 = 22, a clean hit. Damage: Shortsword 1d6 (2), Sneak Attack 1d6 (5), +3 Dexterity, for 10 piercing damage.\n\nThe bandit has no time to shout before Kira's blade slips between his ribs. He slumps silently to the ground, hidden behind the crates. From your vantage, you see her signal--a quick flash of her hand--then she ducks out of sight, ready for your next command. The other two bandits and Captain Gorvek remain oblivious for now, but the risk of discovery grows each moment.",
