{
  "narration": "Kira tenses at your signal, blade slick with blood and breath held as she melts deeper into the shadows behind the crates. You draw a deep breath and step into the flickering torchlight above the gate, calling out in a deliberately weary, confused voice. 'Hello down there! I seem to be lost. Anyone spare a meal and a warm place to sleep?' The words echo through the stronghold, instantly shattering the band's easy camaraderie.\n\nThe nearest bandit warrior jolts to his feet, hand on his sword, while the second narrows his eyes in suspicion. Captain Gorvek turns sharply, his green-glinting gaze fixing on you. He snarls, 'Who the blazes...?' and gestures for his men to fan out, flanking the fire pit. The warriors tense, one drawing a crossbow while the other hefts a battered spear.\n\nGorvek strides forward, chin high, voice harsh. 'You picked the wrong night to stumble into my camp, stranger. Drop your weapon and come down here, nice and slow.'\n\nKira shifts her weight, ready to strike again if you give the cue. For now, you have their attention--but the bandits' posture is openly hostile, weapons drawn and suspicion sharp. The moment teeters on a knife's edge: you could try to talk your way closer, attempt a surprise attack, or use the distraction to unleash Kira on the nearest bandit.\n\nWhat do you do, Eirik? Attempt persuasion, deliver a surprise attack, or give Kira the signal to strike again? The stronghold is poised for violence, and the next seconds will decide whether you have the upper hand.",
