{
  "narration": "As you raise your arms in feigned surrender and move slowly down the platform, careful to keep yourself partially behind a stack of crates to obscure the line of sight for the crossbowman, the tension in the stronghold sharpens. Your posture draws wary attention but not immediate violence; the bandits remain suspicious but are not yet ready to fire blindly. \n\nCaptain Gorvek barks, 'Keep your aim on him, but don't shoot unless he does something stupid.' The crossbowman narrows his eyes, but your careful approach and casual banter seem to confuse him, making his aim uncertain. You can almost feel the bandit's grip loosen just enough for Kira to take advantage.\n\nIn the shadows behind the stacked crates, Kira nods at your subtle signal and slinks into position behind the remaining weak-looking warrior. She moves like a shadow cast by the firelight, her shortsword drawn, guided by your earlier encouragement and her own confidence in the cover of chaos.\n\nKira attempts a Stealth check to stay hidden as she closes in: Rolling... d20 (15) + 6 = 21. The bandits, entirely focused on you, fail to notice her at all.\n\nWithout hesitation, Kira strikes: Attack roll... d20 (18) + 5 = 23. The blade slips between the bandit's ribs in a swift, practiced motion. Damage: Shortsword 1d6 (3), Sneak Attack 1d6 (6), +3 Dex = 12 piercing damage. The bandit collapses with a soft gasp, his body slumping behind the crates, out of sight of the others.\n\nThe crossbowman and the remaining warrior tense, not yet realizing their numbers are dwindling. Gorvek, frowning, steps closer to you, squinting suspiciously. 'Who are you, really?' he growls. The next few moments will decide whether the ruse holds or chaos erupts.\n\nKira remains hidden, ready to strike again if needed, her presence only a ghost in the shadows. The odds shift further in your favor.",
