  "narration": "Kira gives a quick, approving nod. 'Right, the captain's bound to have something interesting on him.'\n\nTogether, you approach the fallen form of Captain Gorvek. His armor is battered but reinforced with odd metal plates, and strange runes are etched into the leather straps beneath his cloak. Kira kneels and quickly checks for hidden blades or traps, then starts rifling through the captain's gear. \n\nYou find:\n- A heavy iron key, still slick with blood and grime, likely to a locked chest or gate.\n- A pouch holding 16 gold coins, 12 silver, and 7 battered copper coins.\n- A missive with a broken black wax seal and coded script, bearing the sigil of a twisted crow's foot -- possibly a message from Malarok or another dark patron.\n- A polished dagger with the same strange symbols as his armor.\n- A scrap of parchment with a rough map of Thornwood, marked with Xs at the Rangers' Outpost, Hermit's Refuge, and a location deeper into the Northern Corrupted Woods.\n\nKira glances up, lips pursed. 'Looks like he was planning something bigger, or reporting to someone... and this key is too heavy for a coin pouch.' She quietly hands you the gold, raising an eyebrow in case you want to split it or hold onto it for now.\n\nThe fire crackles and the stronghold is eerily quiet, save for your quick breaths and the gentle clink of coins. The rest of the loot and clues await in the crates and supply cache. Kira whispers, 'Think this key matches the chest over there, or shall we check the other bodies first?'",
