  "narration": "You study the parchment and the bundled supplies, letting your faith and years of religious training guide your mind through the tangled web of runes and symbols. The glyphs disturb you at a primal level, but you push past the unease, tracing each mark and whispered intent. The knowledge comes in a rush: the sigils are a hybrid of blasphemous invocations to dark spirits and corrupted prayers twisted from old hymns of warding.\n\nThe vials contain a brew meant to 'soften the soul,' making those who drink or touch it vulnerable to possession or influence by corruptive forces. The herbs aren't merely for ritual--they bind the will of those exposed, preparing them for dark magic. The crystals channel energy, acting as conduits for Malarok's curse, and the parchment is a ritual script for infusing mundane supplies and foodstuffs with this curse. Anyone subsisting on the tainted goods would slowly become open to suggestion, their dreams haunted, their will eroded until they could be compelled to serve their new master.\n\nKira's face darkens as you explain. 'So that's how Malarok turned the bandits. Not just gold and fear, but actual magic--right in their food and water.' She steadies herself, then adds, 'We'll want to show all of this to Elen. If anyone at the outpost is acting strange, this could be why.'\n\nYour discovery is a major clue in the corruption's spread through Thornwood--and may be the key to saving others from Malarok's growing influence. The bundle is dangerous, but in your hands, it may also become a powerful tool for understanding and ending the threat.",
